Auto Show Charity Preview 2023. @intevaproducts wanted to highlight their products’ sustainability, stitching technology, and illuminated stitches, so @lilacpop made a weather-themed dress for me! The top is embroidered with sun rays which light up and spread across. The skirt has raindrops falling into puddles at the bottom which slowly drop into the puddles and turn into a rainstorm. The dress is recyclable and made of the company’s vegan “inteather.” It is programmed with over 2000 energy efficient LED lights. The biggest thank you to Janna and @aidanojr for allowing me to wear this dream dress! 👗 

Dress Designer: @lilacpop 
Company (material, stitching and lightning): @intevaproducts

WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM TO 11 AM TUESDAY 1/9/24 for Livingston, Oakland, Macomb, Washtenaw, Wayne, Lenawee and Monroe Counties.

* Wet snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches. Isolated totals to 5 inches.

* A burst of heavy, wet snow is expected to lead to rapid accumulations Tuesday morning. The combination with strong wind gusts up to 35 mph could result in some downed tree limbs and sporadic power outages. Rising temperatures will cause snow to change to rain by late morning.

WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING for Midland, Bay, Huron, Saginaw, Tuscola, Sanilac, Shiawassee, Genesee, Lapeer and Livingston Counties.

Total snow accumulations of 6 inches or more possible. Winds could gust as high as 50 mph.

*Uncertainty exists regarding the northward progress of the rain/snow line Friday which greatly impacts total snowfall amounts should snow mix with rain or briefly change over to all-rain. I do think at this time it’s fair to think metro Detroit could be in the 3-6” range. Snowfall rates are expected to peak Friday evening with maximum rates near 1 inch per hour across the Tri-Cities and Thumb regions. Very strong winds are expected Saturday with gusts of 40-50 mph possible as arctic air filters in behind the system sending wind chill values into the single digits Saturday.
🚨4Warn Weather Alert Day: 4Warn Weather Meteorologist Ashlee Baracy breaks down what to expect this weekend for the upcoming storm.
